jaspContainer

jaspContainer.Rd

A jaspObject that can contain other jaspObjects

createJaspContainer(
  title = "",
  dependencies = NULL,
  position = NULL,
  initCollapsed = FALSE
)

Arguments

title

String, title of the jaspContainer
dependencies

see jaspObject
position

see jaspObject
initCollapsed

Logical, should the container be collapsed by default?

Method new()

Create a new jaspContainer, however, `createJaspContainer()` is preferred.

Method length()

The number of elements inside the container

Usage

jaspContainerR$length()

Examples

library(jaspResults)

container <- createJaspContainer(title = "This is a container")
container$print()

#> container This is a container
#> 

container[["internal_name_1"]] <- createJaspContainer(title = "name shown to users 1")
container[["internal_name_2"]] <- createJaspContainer(title = "name shown to users 2")
container$print()

#> container This is a container:
#> 	"internal_name_1":
#> 		container name shown to users 1
#> 
#> 	"internal_name_2":
#> 		container name shown to users 2
#> 
#> 

# let's reverse the position
container[["subcontainer1"]]$position <- 2
container[["subcontainer2"]]$position <- 1
container$print()

#> container This is a container:
#> 	"internal_name_1":
#> 		container name shown to users 1
#> 
#> 	"internal_name_2":
#> 		container name shown to users 2
#> 
#>
